
502 GATEWAY ERROR

One server (usually a proxy or gateway) received an invalid response
from another server it was trying to communicate with.

Web applications using reverse proxies (like Nginx, Apache, or load balancers) to forward requests to a backend server (like Spring Boot)

Frontend apps (like React or Angular) making API calls to a backend thatâ€™s down or misconfigured

APIs or microservices that call other services internally

COMMON CAUSES:
Backend server is down
Port mismatch
Incorrect API URL